  "text": "Another interesting feature of ontologies is that they can aid in the creation of similarity metrics. This has already been attempted by many projects for example in [CITATION_1] to gauge the similarity between genes using the GO ontology and by Resnik in [CITATION_2] to gauge the similarity between different words with the WordNet Thesaurus. This technique can aid in the integration of the other sub-projects in HeC such as the DSS by creating a similarity metric based on the HeC ontology, hence creating a common base for the training and classification phases of the DSS. Furthermore the HeC ontology can be used within the project in the creation of ontology based training data, e.g. to classify different diseases; this can be achieved by using the rule base of the ontology within an expert system [24] . The HeC ontology can be used to annotate different data sets such as images for easy access later, creating a semantic image database.",
